partial_progress.details: Phase 1 completed with 6 new derivation-theoretic lemmas. Phase 2 blocked: FPreservingSeed consistency conjecture is FALSE (counterexample found). Phases 3-5 blocked. Phase 6 completed (documentation). forward_F and backward_P sorries remain.

review_reason: FPreservingSeed consistency conjecture is mathematically false. Concrete counterexample found: FContent formulas interact with GContent implications via modus ponens to break seed consistency. The derivation surgery approach (v005) is fundamentally blocked. forward_F and backward_P sorries require a completely different proof strategy. Phase 1 lemmas are preserved as valuable structural facts.

errors.message: FPreservingSeed conjecture ({psi} union GContent(M) union FContent(M) is consistent when F(psi) in M) is FALSE. Counterexample: In integer model with q false at 0, q true at 1, r true only at 0: G(F(r)->neg(q)) in M puts (F(r)->neg(q)) in GContent, F(r) in FContent, and {q, F(r)->neg(q), F(r)} derives bot via modus ponens.
errors.recommendation: Requires fundamentally different approach: refined seed selection, alternative chain topology, or saturation-based construction
